        <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
            <head>Biographical/Historical Information </head>
            <p>Dr. Cadwalader Evans of Philadelphia was the grandson of an immigrant to the city. He
                was also friends with Benjamin Franklin. </p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
            <head>Scope and Content </head>
            <p>Cadwalader Evans is writing to Samuel Wharton about Wharton's family that has
                remained in Philadelphia while Wharton has traveled to London. Much of the
                discussion focuses on innoculating family members against small pox. Evans is also
                interested in trying to produce silk near the Ohio River. He also comments on the
                state of trade in Philadelphia as a result of the trade embargo with England. </p>
        </scopecontent>
